"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/971697","Treasury","false","2018-09-17","<p>Over 92, 000 families have used their childcare accounts by early September 2018, to pay their childcare provider.</p><p> </p><p>The Tax-Free Childcare service opened in April 2017; 2014 forecasts are based on a different roll-out profile and so it is not robust to compare the two.</p>","South West Norfolk","Elizabeth Truss",,"2018-09-17T09:28:17.527Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/971697/answer","Biography information for Elizabeth Truss","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/971697/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/971697/answer",,,,,,,,,"14","Treasury","Treasury","2018-09-11","Children: Day Care","1","House of Commons","To ask the Chancellor of the Exchequer, how many parents currently benefit from tax-free childcare; and how many parents were projected to benefit at this stage of the roll-out in the March 2014 forecast.","false","Biography information for Stephanie Peacock","Barnsley East","Stephanie Peacock","173624"
